	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hmm. Can't really say, but after perusing my most recently-played soundtracks, I <em>can</em> say I highly recommend anything by Motoaki Takenouchi (Jewel Master, Landstalker, Shining Force II). "Treasure Hunter Nigel" from Landstalker used to lodge itself in my brain for hours when I was younger. "Jewel Master" from the game of the same name is also terribly catchy.
<br />
<br />[edit]
<br />PUGGSY. A nice, clean-sounding soundtrack by Matt Furniss and Shaun Hollingworth with some fantastic DAC drums. Something about the fake bell instrument they use really tickles my eardrums, and it probably has <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q4vVzuKJMHM&amp;feature=related" class="postlink">one of the happiest, bounciest ending themes I've ever heard.</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
